102
11:43.360 --> 11:51.200
Effective use of VQE also requires that we know attributes of our target state and can select a good physically

103
11:51.200 --> 11:57.680
motivated initial state as well as a good anzot with relatively few variational parameters. This can be

104
11:57.680 --> 12:05.839
quite challenging. VQE demonstrates how the strengths of classical and quantum computers can be combined

105
12:05.839 --> 12:13.600
without adding more recent methods. VQE does not help us solve problems that are intractable for classical computers, but

106
12:13.600 --> 12:21.440
it continues to play a role in algorithm development. And VQE also teaches us that transferring a step from classical

107
12:21.440 --> 12:27.680
to quantum computers is neither better nor worse for all purposes. Rather, it

108
12:27.680 --> 12:34.079
changes what factors determine the efficiency of your algorithm. This is an important general lesson in quantum

109
12:34.079 --> 12:38.200
classical hybrid computing.
